<%- layout('layouts/boilerplate')%>

<div class="about-wrapper container py-5">

  <!-- Title Section -->
  <div class="text-center mb-5 fade-slide">
    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold about-title">Terms & Conditions</h1>
    <p class="lead text-muted about-subtitle">
      Please read these terms carefully before using WhatIfWorld.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Intro Section -->
  <div class="glass-card p-4 mb-5 fade-up">
    <p class="text-muted mb-0">
      By accessing or using WhatIfWorld, you agree to follow all guidelines, rules,
      and conditions mentioned in this page. These terms ensure safety, fairness,
      and responsible usage for all users of our platform.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Sections -->
  <div class="row g-4">

    <!-- Using Our Service -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">1. Use of Our Service</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          WhatIfWorld allows users to create, explore, and share “What If?” scenarios
          using AI-powered predictions. You agree to use the platform responsibly and
          avoid submitting harmful, offensive, or misleading content.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Account Requirements -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">2. Account Requirements</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          A valid account is required to create scenarios, share posts, like, or comment.
          Without logging in, you may only view community posts. You are responsible
          for keeping your login information safe.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Scenario Validation -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">3. Scenario Validation</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          Our AI automatically checks every submitted scenario. If a scenario is
          unclear, harmful, or does not follow proper structure, the system may block it
          and display an error message. This is done to maintain quality and safety.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Community Guidelines -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">4. Community Guidelines</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          You may share your scenario results publicly. Other users can like,
          comment, and engage with your posts. You agree not to post inappropriate,
          abusive, or illegal content. You can delete your own posts at any time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- User Content Ownership -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">5. Ownership of User Content</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          You own the scenarios and posts you create. By sharing content publicly,
          you allow WhatIfWorld to display and distribute it within the platform
          for other users to view and interact with.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Restrictions -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">6. Restrictions</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          You agree not to:
          <ul class="text-muted mt-2">
            <li>Submit harmful or illegal scenarios</li>
            <li>Use the platform for harassment or spam</li>
            <li>Try to harm, hack, or misuse the system</li>
            <li>Impersonate another person or user</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- AI Predictions -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">7. AI Predictions Disclaimer</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          All predictions generated by the AI are hypothetical and may not reflect
          real-world outcomes. They are meant for learning, creativity, and analysis,
          not for professional advice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Termination -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">8. Termination</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          We may restrict or suspend your account if you engage in harmful behavior
          or violate these terms. Currently, account deletion is not available, but 
          users can delete their posts at any time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Future Updates -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">9. Updates to These Terms</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          We may update or modify these Terms & Conditions as the platform grows.
          Any major changes will be communicated through the website.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Contact Us -->
    <div class="col-md-6 fade-up">
      <div class="glass-card p-4 h-100">
        <h4 class="fw-bold">10. Contact Us</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          For questions, issues, or suggestions, you can reach us through the 
          contact form on our website. We are happy to assist you anytime.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

